The MPEG-1 specification is divided into five parts: Systems, Video, Audio, Compliance testing, and Software simulation.
The Systems part (ISO/IEC 11172-1) focuses on defining the overall architecture of the system, including the format of data and the requirements for decoding and synchronization.
Part 2 (ISO/IEC 11172-2) specifically deals with the compression and encoding of video in MPEG-1.
The Audio part (ISO/IEC 11172-3) centers around the compression and encoding of audio.
Part 4 (ISO/IEC 11172-4) addresses compliance testing, which plays a critical role in ensuring that all equipment and components meet the requirements set out in the ISO/IEC 11172 specification.
